      <!-- Club Mania (1st Semester) -->
      <div class="event">
          <h3>General Rules :-</h3>
          <p>
            <b>1. Eligibility:</b><br>
             Open to all students currently enrolled in any college.<br>
             Participants must present a valid student ID during registration.<br>
            <b>2. Team Composition:</b><br>
             Each team must consist of 2–4 members.<br>
             Cross-college teams are allowed.<br>
            <b>3. Registration:</b><br>
             All teams must register before Registration Deadline.<br>
             Late or incomplete registrations will not be accepted.<br>
            <b>4. Company Selection:</b><br>
             Teams will be called one by one to select a company’s name from a draw.<br>
             Each team must design the UI for the selected company based on the
               provided brief.<br>
             The company assignment is final and cannot be changed.
          </p>
          <h3>Specific Guidelines :-</h3>
          <p>
            <b>1. Theme:</b><br>
             The design must reflect the chosen company’s brand identity and target
            audience.<br>
            <b>2. Tools:</b><br>
             Participants can use any tools of their choice, including HTML, CSS,
            JavaScript, frameworks (e.g., React, Vue, Angular), and AI-based tools (e.g.,
            ChatGPT, DALL·E, GitHub Copilot).<br>
             Internet usage is allowed for resource gathering, designing, and AI
            assistance.<br>
            <b>3. Resources:</b><br>
             Organizers will provide required assets like logos, brand guidelines, and any
            additional material related to the selected company<br>
            <b>4. Collaboration:</b><br>
             Teams must work independently and are prohibited from sharing ideas with
            other teams.<br>
             Queries should be directed to the event coordinators or mentors.<br>
            <b>4. Submissions and Presentation:</b><br>
             Final submissions must be a fully functional web project.<br>
            <b>Accepted submission formats:</b><br>
               o A hosted link (e.g., on GitHub Pages, Netlify, or any hosting platform).<br>
               o Demonstration via localhost is also accepted, provided the project
                 runs without issues.<br>
             Source code must be uploaded to a GitHub repository with appropriate
            documentation.<br>
          </p>
          <h3>Judging Criteria :-</h3>
          <p>
             Creativity (25%): Innovation and originality in design.<br>
             User Experience (UX) (25%): Intuitive navigation and user-friendliness.<br>
             Visual Appeal (20%): Effective use of branding, layout, and typography.<br>
             Functionality (15%): Practicality and alignment with the company’s needs.<br>
             Presentation (15%): Ability to explain and justify design decisions.<br>
            <b>Scoring System:</b><br>
                Each criterion will be scored out of 10.<br>
                Total possible score: 100 points.
          </p>
          <h3>Code of Conduct :-</h3>
          <p>
             Maintain respect and professionalism towards all participants, judges, and
            organizers.<br>
             Plagiarism or use of pre-designed templates is strictly prohibited.<br>
             Teams must not disrupt other participants or interfere with their work.<br>
             Any disputes must be addressed through the coordinators.<br>
             Disqualification Conditions
          </p>
          <h3>Disqualification Condition :-</h3>
